Newspaper reports suggest that new intelligence boss was arrested for being in possession of stolen property in 1993. JOHANNESBURG Newly appointed crime intelligence boss Pat Mokushane has been reported to have a criminal record.The 57-year-old was apparently found guilty of violating the national road traffic act in 2002- and his subsequent appointment to the high ranking job is now being questioned.Newspaper reports suggest that Mokushane was arrested for being in possession of stolen property in 1993.Police spokesman Vish Naidoo says the uMkhonto weSizwe veteran's appointment as acting head is between employer and employee, and that nothing about it would be discussed on the media space. If and when we see that there is any public interest in this matter and we see a need to do so we will communicate it externally. 